{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775884539875,"sessionID":"ses_28508bd72ffeXIhFXu0VWKX43w","part":{"id":"prt_d7af797a8001oXvWSRpKX2I8zJ","messageID":"msg_d7af77b0d001bcBhjhVXZIw6Gz","sessionID":"ses_28508bd72ffeXIhFXu0VWKX43w","type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"toolu_tool-1709c43ed92b4f30b4bd5c73aaf14aad","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"ls -la /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd","description":"List cmd directory contents"},"output":"total 36\ndrwxr-xr-x  9 root root 4096 Apr 11 07:55 .\ndrwxr-xr-x 24 root root 4096 Apr 11 12:22 ..\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 07:33 agentcube\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 07:35 agentcube-util\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 07:07 agentd\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 07:34 agent-runtime\ndrwxr-xr-x  8 root root 4096 Apr 11 10:57 cli\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 07:34 code-interpreter\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 06:04 picod\n","metadata":{"output":"total 36\ndrwxr-xr-x  9 root root 4096 Apr 11 07:55 .\ndrwxr-xr-x 24 root root 4096 Apr 11 12:22 ..\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 07:33 agentcube\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 07:35 agentcube-util\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 07:07 agentd\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 07:34 agent-runtime\ndrwxr-xr-x  8 root root 4096 Apr 11 10:57 cli\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 07:34 code-interpreter\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 06:04 picod\n","exit":0,"description":"List cmd directory contents","truncated":false},"title":"List cmd directory contents","time":{"start":1775884539853,"end":1775884539874}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775884539891,"sessionID":"ses_28508bd72ffeXIhFXu0VWKX43w","part":{"id":"prt_d7af79531001z7MFrVAlFiIXQ7","messageID":"msg_d7af77b0d001bcBhjhVXZIw6Gz","sessionID":"ses_28508bd72ffeXIhFXu0VWKX43w","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-58d4310c415645fe8fc4b53ac96c470b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-033/delta-spec.md","limit":200},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-033/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-033 — Makefile 构建目标体系 Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## AR Metadata\n4: - **AR ID**: AR-033\n5: - **Title**: Makefile 构建目标体系\n6: - **Module**: root\n7: - **Language**: Makefile\n8: - **Size**: M\n9: - **Status**: Implementation Required\n10: \n11: ## Purpose\n12: \n13: This delta specification provides comprehensive acceptance criteria for the Makefile build target system in the AgentCube project. It defines requirements for a unified build system that manages building, testing, cleaning, code quality checks, and Docker image builds for both Go and Python components. The specification ensures a standardized, efficient, and developer-friendly build interface with detailed GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios to verify proper implementation of all build targets and features.\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Makefile structure and organization\n18: \n19: The system SHALL implement a modular Makefile structure with a main Makefile in the root directory and organized sub-Makefiles for different language and functional areas.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Root Makefile exists and is properly structured\n22: - **GIVEN** the AgentCube project root directory\n23: - **WHEN** examining the directory structure\n24: - **THEN** a Makefile SHALL exist in the root directory\n25: - **AND** the Makefile SHALL be the main entry point for all build operations\n26: - **AND** the Makefile SHALL include sub-Makefiles from .makefiles/ directory\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: .makefiles/ directory exists with sub-Makefiles\n29: - **GIVEN** the .makefiles/ directory\n30: - **WHEN** examining its contents\n31: - **THEN** go.mk SHALL exist for Go-specific build rules\n32: - **AND** python.mk SHALL exist for Python-specific build rules\n33: - **AND** docker.mk SHALL exist for Docker-specific build rules\n34: - **AND** test.mk SHALL exist for test-specific rules\n35: - **AND** lint.mk SHALL exist for lint/format-specific rules\n36: - **AND** each sub-Makefile SHALL be properly included in the main Makefile\n37: \n38: #### Scenario: scripts/ directory exists for build scripts\n39: - **GIVEN** the scripts/ directory\n40: - **WHEN** examining its contents\n41: - **THEN** build.sh SHALL exist for complex build operations\n42: - **AND** test.sh SHALL exist for test execution scripts\n43: - **AND** release.sh SHALL exist for release preparation scripts\n44: - **AND** scripts SHALL be executable (chmod +x)\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: bin/ directory exists for build artifacts\n47: - **GIVEN** the bin/ directory\n48: - **WHEN** examining its structure\n49: - **THEN** the directory SHALL exist or be created on first build\n50: - **AND** the directory SHALL be in .gitignore\n51: - **AND** build artifacts SHALL be placed in bin/ by default\n52: - **AND** cross-platform artifacts SHALL be placed in bin/<platform>/ subdirectories\n53: \n54: ### Requirement: Go build targets\n55: \n56: The system SHALL provide comprehensive build targets for all Go binaries in the AgentCube project.\n57: \n58: #### Scenario: build-go target builds all Go binaries\n59: - **GIVEN** a clean AgentCube project with Go source code\n60: - **WHEN** running `make build-go`\n61: - **THEN** all Go binaries SHALL be compiled successfully\n62: - **AND** binaries SHALL be placed in bin/ directory\n63: - **AND** the following binaries SHALL be built: agentd, picod, cli\n64: - **AND** build status SHALL be displayed with color-coded output\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: build target builds both Go and Python components\n67: - **GIVEN** a clean AgentCube project\n68: - **WHEN** running `make build`\n69: - **THEN** `make build-go` SHALL be invoked\n70: - **AND** `make build-python` SHALL be invoked\n71: - **AND** both Go and Python artifacts SHALL be built successfully\n72: - **AND** the build SHALL complete without errors\n73: \n74: #### Scenario: Individual Go component build targets exist\n75: - **GIVEN** the Makefile Go targets\n76: - **WHEN** examining the available targets\n77: - **THEN** build-agentd target SHALL exist\n78: - **AND** build-picod target SHALL exist\n79: - **AND** build-router target SHALL exist (if router exists)\n80: - **AND** build-cli target SHALL exist\n81: - **AND** each target SHALL build only its respective component\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: build-agentd target builds agentd binary\n84: - **GIVEN** the agentd source code in cmd/agentd/\n85: - **WHEN** running `make build-agentd`\n86: - **THEN** agentd binary SHALL be compiled\n87: - **AND** the binary SHALL be placed at bin/agentd\n88: - **AND** the binary SHALL be executable\n89: - **AND** build metadata (version, commit) SHALL be embedded\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: build-picod target builds picod binary\n92: - **GIVEN** the picod source code in cmd/picod/\n93: - **WHEN** running `make build-picod`\n94: - **THEN** picod binary SHALL be compiled\n95: - **AND** the binary SHALL be placed at bin/picod\n96: - **AND** the binary SHALL be executable\n97: - **AND** build metadata SHALL be embedded\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: build-cli target builds CLI tool\n100: - **GIVEN** the CLI source code in cmd/cli/\n101: - **WHEN** running `make build-cli`\n102: - **THEN** CLI binary SHALL be compiled\n103: - **AND** the binary SHALL be placed at bin/agentcube\n104: - **AND** the binary SHALL be executable\n105: - **AND** the binary SHALL respond to --version flag\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Go build supports cross-platform compilation\n108: - **GIVEN** the Go build targets\n109: - **WHEN** setting GOOS and GOARCH environment variables\n110: - **THEN** the build SHALL compile for the target platform\n111: - **AND** the binary SHALL be placed in bin/<platform>/ subdirectory\n112: - **AND** supported platforms SHALL include: linux/amd64, linux/arm64, darwin/amd64, darwin/arm64\n113: \n114: #### Scenario: Go build supports release mode\n115: - **GIVEN** the Go build targets\n116: - **WHEN** setting BUILD_MODE=release\n117: - **THEN** build flags SHALL include -ldflags=\"-s -w\" for stripping\n118: - **AND** debug information SHALL be removed\n119: - **AND** the binary size SHALL be minimized\n120: - **AND** the binary SHALL be production-ready\n121: \n122: #### Scenario: Go build supports dev mode with race detection\n123: - **GIVEN** the Go build targets\n124: - **WHEN** setting BUILD_MODE=dev (default)\n125: - **THEN** build flags SHALL include -race for race detection\n126: - **AND** debug information SHALL be included\n127: - **AND** the binary SHALL be suitable for development\n128: \n129: #### Scenario: Go build uses build cache efficiently\n130: - **GIVEN** a previous successful build\n131: - **WHEN** running `make build-go` again without source changes\n132: - **THEN** the build SHALL use cached artifacts\n133: - **AND** the build time SHALL be significantly faster\n134: - **AND** \"cache hit\" messages SHALL be displayed\n135: \n136: ### Requirement: Python build targets\n137: \n138: The system SHALL provide comprehensive build targets for Python packages in the AgentCube project.\n139: \n140: #### Scenario: build-python target builds Python package\n141: - **GIVEN** a clean AgentCube project with Python source code\n142: - **WHEN** running `make build-python`\n143: - **THEN** the Python package SHALL be built as wheel\n144: - **AND** the wheel SHALL be placed in dist/ directory\n145: - **AND** the source distribution (sdist) SHALL also be built\n146: - **AND** build SHALL complete successfully\n147: \n148: #### Scenario: install-python target installs Python dependencies\n149: - **GIVEN** a Python environment with pip\n150: - **WHEN** running `make install-python`\n151: - **THEN** all production dependencies SHALL be installed\n152: - **AND** dependencies SHALL be read from requirements.txt or pyproject.toml\n153: - **AND** installation SHALL complete without errors\n154: - **AND** installed packages SHALL be listed\n155: \n156: #### Scenario: install-dev target installs development dependencies\n157: - **GIVEN** a Python environment with pip\n158: - **WHEN** running `make install-dev`\n159: - **THEN** all development dependencies SHALL be installed\n160: - **AND** dependencies SHALL include: pytest, ruff, mypy, black\n161: - **AND** installation SHALL complete without errors\n162: - **AND** development environment SHALL be ready\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: Python build uses virtual environment\n165: - **GIVEN** the Python build targets\n166: - **WHEN** VIRTUAL_ENV environment variable is set\n167: - **THEN** the build SHALL use the virtual environment's Python\n168: - **AND** packages SHALL be installed in the virtual environment\n169: - **AND** the virtual environment SHALL not be affected by system Python\n170: \n171: #### Scenario: Python build respects PYTHON_VERSION variable\n172: - **GIVEN** the Python build targets\n173: - **WHEN** setting PYTHON_VERSION to a specific version (e.g., 3.11)\n174: - **THEN** the build SHALL use the specified Python version\n175: - **AND** the version SHALL be validated\n176: - **AND** an error SHALL occur if the version is not available\n177: \n178: ### Requirement: Test targets\n179: \n180: The system SHALL provide comprehensive test targets for running Go and Python tests.\n181: \n182: #### Scenario: test target runs all tests\n183: - **GIVEN** a built AgentCube project\n184: - **WHEN** running `make test`\n185: - **THEN** `make test-go` SHALL be invoked\n186: - **AND** `make test-python` SHALL be invoked\n187: - **AND** all tests SHALL pass\n188: - **AND** test summary SHALL be displayed with pass/fail counts\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: test-go target runs Go tests\n191: - **GIVEN** the Go source code with tests\n192: - **WHEN** running `make test-go`\n193: - **THEN** all Go tests SHALL be executed\n194: - **AND** tests SHALL run with verbose output (-v flag)\n195: - **AND** test coverage SHALL be collected\n196: - **AND** test results SHALL be summarized\n197: \n198: #### Scenario: test-python target runs Python tests\n199: - **GIVEN** the Python source code with tests\n200: - **WHEN** running `make test-python`\n\n(Showing lines 1-200 of 959. Use offset=201 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-033 — Makefile 构建目标体系 Delta Specification\n\n## AR Metadata\n- **AR ID**: AR-033\n- **Title**: Makefile 构建目标体系\n- **Module**: root\n- **Language**: Makefile\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: Implementation Required\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis delta specification provides comprehensive acceptance criteria for the Makefile build target system in the AgentCube project. It defines requirements for a unified build system that manages building, testing, cleaning, code quality checks, and Docker image builds for both Go and Python components. The specification ensures a standardized, efficient, and developer-friendly build interface with detailed GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios to verify proper implementation of all build targets and features.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Makefile structure and organization\n\nThe system SHALL implement a modular Makefile structure with a main Makefile in the root directory and organized sub-Makefiles for different language and functional areas.\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-033/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775884539848,"end":1775884539888}}}}
