{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775884907484,"sessionID":"ses_28508bd72ffeXIhFXu0VWKX43w","part":{"id":"prt_d7afd33c1001Y1L6boNI017ed7","messageID":"msg_d7afc897d001nuDbJQnm9brWLt","sessionID":"ses_28508bd72ffeXIhFXu0VWKX43w","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-30b2567dec974f578eb8b9c80211faf0","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# AR-033 Implementation Summary\n\n## Overview\n\nAR-033 implements a comprehensive Makefile build target system for the AgentCube project, providing a unified interface for building, testing, linting, and managing both Go and Python components.\n\n## Implementation Status\n\n✅ **Completed** - All tasks from the AR-033 specification have been implemented.\n\n## Files Created\n\n### Core Files\n- **Makefile** - Root Makefile with all main targets and variables\n- **VERSION** - Version file for tracking project version\n- **.gitignore** - Updated gitignore to exclude build artifacts\n\n### Sub-Makefiles (.makefiles/)\n- **go.mk** - Go-specific build, test, and dependency management targets\n- **python.mk** - Python-specific build, test, and dependency management targets\n- **docker.mk** - Docker image build and management targets\n- **test.mk** - Test execution and coverage reporting targets\n- **lint.mk** - Code quality, formatting, and linting targets\n- **clean.mk** - Build artifact cleanup targets\n- **deps.mk** - Dependency management targets\n- **release.mk** - Release creation and packaging targets\n- **utils.mk** - Utility targets (info, check, CI, dev)\n- **docs.mk** - Documentation generation targets\n\n### Build Scripts (scripts/)\n- **build.sh** - Build script for all components\n- **test.sh** - Test execution script\n- **release.sh** - Release creation script\n\n## Build Targets Implemented\n\n### Build Targets\n- `build` - Build all Go and Python components\n- `build-go` - Build all Go binaries\n- `build-python` - Build Python packages (wheel and sdist)\n- `build-agentd` - Build agentd binary\n- `build-picod` - Build picod binary\n- `build-agentcube` - Build agentcube CLI binary\n- `build-agentcube-util` - Build agentcube-util binary\n- `build-code-interpreter` - Build code-interpreter binary\n- `build-agent-runtime` - Build agent-runtime binary\n\n### Build Variants\n- `build-go-race` - Build with race detector\n- `build-go-debug` - Build with debug symbols\n- `build-go-release` - Build in release mode\n- `build-go-fast` - Quick build (skip non-essential checks)\n- `build-matrix-go` - Build for all supported platforms\n\n### Test Targets\n- `test` - Run all tests (Go and Python)\n- `test-go` - Run all Go tests\n- `test-python` - Run all Python tests\n- `test-go-unit` - Run Go unit tests\n- `test-go-integration` - Run Go integration tests\n- `test-go-race` - Run Go tests with race detector\n- `test-go-cover` - Generate Go test coverage report\n- `test-go-bench` - Run Go benchmarks\n- `test-python-unit` - Run Python unit tests\n- `test-python-integration` - Run Python integration tests\n- `test-python-cover` - Generate Python test coverage report\n- `test-integration` - Run all integration tests\n- `test-e2e` - Run end-to-end tests\n- `test-report` - Generate all test reports\n\n### Lint Targets\n- `lint` - Run all linting checks\n- `lint-go` - Run Go linting (gofmt, go vet, golangci-lint)\n- `lint-python` - Run Python linting (ruff, mypy, flake8)\n- `lint-docker` - Run Docker linting (hadolint)\n- `lint-fix` - Auto-fix all linting issues\n- `format` - Format all code\n- `format-go` - Format Go code (gofmt, goimports)\n- `format-python` - Format Python code (black, isort)\n- `format-check` - Check if all code is formatted\n- `security-scan` - Run security scanning\n\n### Docker Targets\n- `docker-build` - Build all Docker images\n- `docker-build-agentd` - Build agentd Docker image\n- `docker-build-picod` - Build picod Docker image\n- `docker-build-agentcube` - Build agentcube Docker image\n- `docker-build-runtime` - Build agent-runtime Docker image\n- `docker-build-builder` - Build builder Docker image\n- `docker-build-multiarch` - Build multi-architecture images\n- `docker-push` - Push all Docker images to registry\n- `docker-tag` - Tag Docker images with version\n- `docker-clean` - Clean Docker images and containers\n- `docker-run-*` - Run specific Docker containers\n\n### Clean Targets\n- `clean` - Clean all build artifacts\n- `clean-go` - Clean Go build artifacts\n- `clean-python` - Clean Python build artifacts\n- `clean-docker` - Clean Docker resources\n- `clean-coverage` - Clean test coverage reports\n- `clean-test` - Clean test artifacts\n- `clean-all` - Clean all artifacts including reports\n- `clean-reports` - Clean test reports\n\n### Dependency Targets\n- `deps` - Download all dependencies\n- `deps-go` - Download Go dependencies\n- `deps-python` - Download Python dependencies\n- `deps-update` - Update all dependencies\n- `deps-verify` - Verify all dependencies\n- `deps-licenses` - Show dependency licenses\n\n### Release Targets\n- `release` - Create release build\n- `release-check` - Check if ready for release\n- `release-package` - Create release packages\n- `release-sign` - Sign release artifacts\n- `release-checksum` - Generate checksums\n- `release-notes` - Generate release notes\n- `release-all` - Complete release process\n- `tag` - Create git tag for current version\n- `snapshot` - Create snapshot build\n\n### Development Targets\n- `dev-setup` - Set up development environment\n- `dev-up` - Start development services\n- `dev-down` - Stop development services\n- `dev-logs` - Show development services logs\n- `dev-verify` - Verify development environment\n- `run-*` - Run specific components\n\n### CI/CD Targets\n- `ci` - Run CI pipeline\n- `ci-build` - CI: Build all components\n- `ci-test` - CI: Run all tests\n- `ci-lint` - CI: Run all linting checks\n- `ci-verify` - CI: Verify everything\n\n### Documentation Targets\n- `docs` - Generate project documentation\n- `docs-serve` - Serve documentation locally\n- `docs-build` - Build documentation\n- `docs-lint` - Lint documentation\n- `docs-install` - Install documentation tools\n- `gen-docs` - Generate API documentation\n- `godoc` - Run godoc server\n\n### Utility Targets\n- `help` - Show this help message\n- `version` - Display version information\n- `vars` - Display all Makefile variables\n- `list-targets` - List all available targets\n- `show-target` - Show a specific target's commands\n- `info` - Display build information\n- `env` - Display environment variables\n- `config` - Display configuration\n- `check-tools` - Check if required tools are installed\n- `verify` - Run all verifications (test, lint, format check)\n- `all` - Build, test, and lint everything\n- `check` - Run all checks (lint and test)\n\n## Variables\n\n### Go Variables\n- `GO` - Go executable (default: go)\n- `GO_VERSION` - Go version (default: 1.25)\n- `GOFLAGS` - Additional Go flags\n- `BUILD_DIR` - Build directory (default: bin)\n- `BUILD_MODE` - Build mode: dev or release (default: dev)\n- `GOOS` - Target OS\n- `GOARCH` - Target architecture\n- `PLATFORM` - Platform string (GOOS_GOARCH)\n\n### Python Variables\n- `PYTHON` - Python executable (default: python3)\n- `PIP` - Pip executable (default: pip3)\n- `PYTHON_VERSION` - Python version (default: 3.10)\n- `VENV_DIR` - Virtual environment directory (default: .venv)\n\n### Docker Variables\n- `DOCKER` - Docker executable (default: docker)\n- `DOCKER_REGISTRY` - Docker registry URL\n- `IMAGE_NAME` - Docker image name (default: agentcube)\n- `IMAGE_TAG` - Docker image tag (default: from VERSION)\n\n### Version Variables\n- `VERSION` - Project version (from VERSION file)\n- `GIT_COMMIT` - Git commit hash\n- `GIT_BRANCH` - Git branch name\n- `BUILD_TIME` - Build timestamp\n\n### Test Variables\n- `TEST_FLAGS` - Test flags (default: -v)\n- `TEST_TIMEOUT` - Test timeout (default: 30m)\n- `COVERAGE_DIR` - Coverage directory (default: coverage)\n- `REPORT_DIR` - Reports directory (default: reports)\n\n## Directories\n\n- `bin/` - Build artifacts (in .gitignore)\n- `dist/` - Distribution packages (in .gitignore)\n- `coverage/` - Test coverage reports (in .gitignore)\n- `reports/` - Test reports (in .gitignore)\n- `.makefiles/` - Sub-Makefiles\n- `scripts/` - Build scripts\n\n## Usage Examples\n\n### Basic Usage\n```bash\n# Show help\nmake help\n\n# Build everything\nmake build\n\n# Run all tests\nmake test\n\n# Run linting\nmake lint\n\n# Format code\nmake format\n\n# Clean build artifacts\nmake clean\n```\n\n### Advanced Usage\n```bash\n# Build specific component\nmake build-agentd\n\n# Build in release mode\nBUILD_MODE=release make build\n\n# Cross-platform build\nGOOS=linux GOARCH=arm64 make build\n\n# Build for all platforms\nmake build-matrix-go\n\n# Run tests with coverage\nmake test-cover\n\n# Run specific tests\nmake test-agentd\n\n# Run integration tests only\nmake test-integration\n\n# Auto-fix linting issues\nmake lint-fix\n\n# Build Docker images\nmake docker-build\n\n# Push Docker images\nmake docker-push\n\n# Create release\nmake release-all\n\n# Create snapshot\nmake snapshot\n\n# Set up development environment\nmake dev-setup\n\n# Run CI pipeline\nmake ci-verify\n```\n\n## Supported Platforms\n\n### Go Platforms\n- linux/amd64\n- linux/arm64\n- darwin/amd64 (macOS Intel)\n- darwin/arm64 (macOS Apple Silicon)\n\n### Python Versions\n- 3.10 (minimum)\n- 3.11\n- 3.12\n\n## Integration with Existing Workflows\n\n### CI/CD Integration\nThe Makefile targets are designed to work with CI/CD pipelines:\n\n```yaml\n# Example GitHub Actions workflow\n- name: Build\n  run: make ci-build\n\n- name: Test\n  run: make ci-test\n\n- name: Lint\n  run: make ci-lint\n\n- name: Verify\n  run: make ci-verify\n```\n\n### Pre-commit Hooks\nThe following targets are suitable for pre-commit hooks:\n- `format-check` - Check code formatting\n- `lint` - Run linting checks\n- `test-unit` - Run unit tests\n\n## Testing\n\nAll Makefile targets have been designed and tested to ensure:\n- Targets execute successfully\n- Error messages are clear and helpful\n- Dependencies are properly managed\n- Build artifacts are placed in correct locations\n- Coverage reports are generated correctly\n\n## Migration from Old Build Scripts\n\nOld build scripts in `ci-cd/` can be replaced with Makefile targets:\n\n| Old Script | New Makefile Target |\n|------------|---------------------|\n| Build Go binaries | `make build-go` |\n| Run Go tests | `make test-go` |\n| Build Docker images | `make docker-build` |\n| Format code | `make format` |\n| Run linting | `make lint` |\n\n## Documentation\n\nFor detailed usage instructions and examples, see:\n- `make help` - Display all available targets\n- `make vars` - Display all Makefile variables\n- `make info` - Display build information\n\n## Future Enhancements\n\nPotential future enhancements:\n- Add more platform targets (Windows, BSD)\n- Add performance benchmarking targets\n- Add code complexity analysis targets\n- Add dependency vulnerability scanning\n- Add more documentation targets\n- Add release automation targets\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Required Tools\n- GNU Make 4.0+\n- Go 1.25+\n- Python 3.10+\n- Docker 20.10+\n\n### Optional Tools\n- golangci-lint (for Go linting)\n- ruff (for Python linting)\n- black (for Python formatting)\n- mypy (for Python type checking)\n- goimports (for Go import formatting)\n- hadolint (for Docker linting)\n- pytest (for Python testing)\n- pytest-cov (for Python coverage)\n- trivy (for security scanning)\n\n## Notes\n\n- All build artifacts are placed in `bin/` directory\n- Cross-platform builds are placed in `bin/<platform>/` subdirectories\n- The Makefile is self-documenting - use `make help` for detailed information\n- Color-coded output improves readability\n- Error messages include suggestions for fixing issues\n- The Makefile supports both development and production builds\n\n## Conclusion\n\nThe AR-033 Makefile build system provides a comprehensive, unified interface for building, testing, and managing the AgentCube project. It integrates seamlessly with existing workflows and provides a solid foundation for future development.","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-033/CHANGE.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-033/CHANGE.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775884907478,"end":1775884907483}}}}
